Jeremy Corbyn's debut at the Prime Minister's Question Time
Since his election, Mr Corbyn's debut at the Prime Minister's Question Time has been eagerly awaited.
The new Labour leader Jeremy Corbyn is set to make his debut at the Prime Minister's Question Time and take on David Cameron for the first time.
Mr Corbyn will rise to ask the first of his six questions shortly after noon, with his performance likely to be closely monitored by the media and Labour MPs.
