CBS News correspondent Charlie D'Agata reported that even prison inmates were used in the race to build the barbed wire fence between Hungary and Serbia.
In recent months, Hungary has become a significant bottleneck and entry point into the European Union for many war refugees from Syria and elsewhere in the Middle East.
Prime Minister Viktor Orban has insisted, however, that most arrivals are economic refugees seeking a better life, not war refugees who are entitled to protection - a view that is in stark contrast to other EU states, including Germany.
New laws, which came into force at midnight in Hungary, make it a crime to cross the border or damage the four-meter-tall fence the government had built along the southern border with Serbia, and they also impose higher prison sentences for convicted traffickers.
"Because of the situation created by mass migration, the Hungarian government is declaring a state of emergency", government spokesman Zoltan Kovacs told reporters in the southern city of Szeged.
We are very clear: illegal border crossing is a crime.
Parliament has yet to approve the military deployment, which is expected next week, but Associated Press reporters have seen heavily armed soldiers with vehicles and dogs at the border for days.
